					<description><![CDATA[<p>Afresh Raises New Capital To Scale Grocery AI Infrastructure Afresh just raised $34 million to boost its AI grocery platform. Just Climate and High Sage Ventures led the way, while</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/afresh-raises-34-million-expand-ai-grocery-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Afresh Raises $34 Million To Expand AI Grocery Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Afresh Raises New Capital To Scale Grocery AI Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Afresh just raised $34 million to boost its AI grocery platform. Just Climate and High Sage Ventures led the way, while some previous backers chipped in again to push things forward. Afresh plans to get its technology into more grocery stores and improve its AI tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Honestly, running a grocery store isn’t easy. Food goes bad quickly, and profit margins barely leave room to breathe. Every day, managers have to make calls about what to order and what to stock, often relying on a lot of guesswork.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">That makes automating these decisions pretty complicated—especially when it comes to fresh produce. Afresh steps in here, offering real-time data that actually works for how grocery stores operate. The team has been at it for years, building AI systems designed specifically for the ins and outs of grocery stores. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Their platform helps with everything from ordering at each store to planning out the supply chain. Basically, it lets grocery teams make decisions faster and with better results, instead of relying on those old clunky systems that can’t keep up with fresh food demands.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Platform Addresses Fresh Food Complexity And Waste</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fresh food brings its own set of headaches—stuff like short shelf lives and demand that can swing overnight, depending on what’s happening in the world. On top of that, inventory info is usually a mess: missing, out of date, and honestly, not that useful. This all adds up to too much product, too much waste, and money left on the table.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Afresh’s AI platform tackles these problems head-on. It deals with real-time data and updates its recommendations as situations shift. Retailers can nail their stock levels without tossing more food, and stores see stronger availability and profits across the board. But food waste isn’t just a store problem. It drags down the whole supply chain and throws fuel on environmental issues too.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the Food and Agriculture Organization, a large portion of global food production is wasted each year. This creates financial losses and increases emissions across the food system. Afresh aims to reduce this impact through smarter decision-making tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Retailers using the platform have reported measurable improvements. These include reduced shrink, higher sales, and better inventory turnover. The results show that AI can deliver value when applied to real-world operations. This has driven growing interest in the company’s technology.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Adoption Across Retail Networks</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200205" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200205" class="size-full wp-image-200205" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Afresh-2.png" alt="AI-powered retail systems connecting grocery stores, warehouses, and supply chains for real-time inventory and operations management." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200205" class="wp-caption-text">Afresh’s AI platform scaling across retail networks to optimise grocery operations and strengthen supply chain efficiency. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Afresh’s platform is now active in over 12,500 departments across multiple regions. The company works with major grocery retailers to improve operations at scale. Its solutions support both store teams and supply chain managers. This broad adoption reflects strong demand for AI in retail environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has seen rapid growth over the past year. A large share of its lifetime order volume occurred during this period. Revenue has also increased significantly as retailers expand usage. This growth highlights a shift from pilot programmes to full-scale deployment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Retailers are moving towards integrated systems that cover entire operations. Afresh has expanded its platform beyond fresh food into other categories. These include frozen goods, centre store products, and general merchandise. This allows the company to deliver a unified solution across the grocery enterprise.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will support further expansion into these areas. It will also help develop next-generation AI features. These improvements aim to enhance decision-making across all levels of retail operations. The goal is to create a more efficient and responsive supply chain.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/blue-energy-raises-380-million-to-scale-nuclear-power-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Blue Energy Raises $380 Million To Scale Nuclear Power Infrastructure</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Plans Focus On Efficiency And Sustainability</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Afresh plans to use the new capital to scale its platform and team. Investment will focus on product development and customer deployment. The company is also exploring new use cases within the grocery </span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/science/ecosystem" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">ecosystem</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. These include production planning and distribution centre optimisation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Food waste remains a major challenge in the global economy. A significant portion of food is lost before reaching consumers. This creates both financial and environmental costs. Afresh addresses this issue by improving demand forecasting and inventory control.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has already stopped millions of pounds of food from going to waste. That’s a real sign of what AI can actually do to make a difference. Retailers get better at making decisions, waste less, and make more money—so of course they want to keep using this kind of tech.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">What makes Afresh stand out is its hands-on approach. They don’t just chase theoretical solutions; they’re out solving everyday problems. That’s how they’ve earned trust and built strong relationships with retail partners. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It’s also why people see Afresh as a leader when it comes to grocery AI. The industry isn’t standing still, either. More and more, retailers want smart systems that keep up with the real world. Afresh wants to make sure they offer that flexibility as their platform grows. </span></p>
