					<description><![CDATA[<p>Smart Robotics, one of the global leaders in embodied AI and intralogistics automation, announced that it has successfully closed a Series A of €10M. This equity raise, announced today, will</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/smart-robotics-raises-e10m-to-scale-ai-picking-in-europe/" data-wpel-link="internal">Smart Robotics Raises €10M to Scale AI Picking in Europe</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://smart-robotics.io/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Smart Robotics</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, one of the global leaders in embodied AI and intralogistics automation, announced that it has successfully closed a Series A of €10M. This equity </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/recursive-superintelligence-raises-500m-funding-round/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">raise</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, announced today, will be used to fund the company&#8217;s expansion throughout the continent and to further develop its unique AI-based control layer for ultra-fast robotic picking within complex warehouses.</span></p>
<p>Rotterdamse Havendraken headed the Round and saw good interest from, among others, Innovation Industries and the Dutch family office Ernij. This round bolstered the business, indicating increased peer confidence in &#8220;physical AI,&#8221; paired with hardware to address biggest problem spaces.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Addressing the Logistics Bottleneck</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2015 by Heico Sandeè, Smart Robotics has been developing its decades-old &#8220;full stack&#8221; method for automated picking. With rising demand from e-commerce and persistent labour shortages throughout Europe, many warehouses are unable to turn up quickly enough. Robotic pick-and-place, finding, grabbing and sorting a wide range of products is still one of the hardest processes to scale.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200181" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200181" class="size-large wp-image-200181" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Factory-with-robots-1024x683.jpg" alt="Factory with robots" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200181" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike other companies that sell standard, off-the-shelf hardware, Smart Robotics supplies fully customised, ready-to-use robotic cells. As claimed by the company, these systems are capable of achieving throughput rates of up to 1,000 picks per hour at 99.5% uptime, which compares favourably with or even surpasses human operators.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/recursive-superintelligence-raises-500m-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Recursive Superintelligence Raises $500M Funding Round</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Data-Driven Advantage</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The &#8220;secret sauce&#8221; behind the performance of Smart Robotics is its huge real-world experience. The company officially crossed the one billion successful picks mark, making it arguably the first European company to build such a huge operational dataset.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;What really differs us is the real-world data scale we have,&#8221; said the company in a recent statement. Every pick done by an already deployed robot generates a feedback loop, which continuously enhances the AI control system, enabling robots to deal with an even higher SKU variability and warehouse workflow complexity. With more than 120 robots on the field, Smart Robotics uses this data to set a huge competitive barrier.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling for the Future</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The €10 million Series A investment will help Smart Robotics bolster three key areas:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>European Growth</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: A strengthened sales team and local implementation support will </span><b>enable penetration into new markets outside of the Netherlands.</b></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product Innovation</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: An entirely new product line will be introduced to supplement its current shelving and palletizing clutches.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>AI Evolution</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: The proprietary AI control layer will be further developed to ensure that Smart Robotics&#8217; solutions continue to adapt to the increasingly dynamic needs of retail &amp; manufacturing supply chains.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We saw a large hole in logistics automation,&#8221; said co-CEO Felix Schmidt. &#8220;By combining our software tech stack with customized robotic hardware, we are building systems that can think better and support humans in production and warehouse settings.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>As intra-Europe focuses on reindustrializing and powering digital capability, Smart Robotics will help ensure competitiveness. With this new Series A, the Eindhoven innovator is ready to become a key player in Europe’s intralogistics future.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/smart-robotics-raises-e10m-to-scale-ai-picking-in-europe/" data-wpel-link="internal">Smart Robotics Raises €10M to Scale AI Picking in Europe</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
