					<description><![CDATA[<p>AI-powered market research platform, Ideally announced today the closing of a $10 million (US) Series A funding round. The announcement coincides with the U.S. debut of Ideally Canvas, a new</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ideally-launches-ideally-canvas-after-10m-series-a/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ideally Launches Ideally Canvas After $10M Series A</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI-powered market research platform, </span><a href="https://www.goideally.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ideally </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced today the closing of a $10 million (US) Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/recursive-superintelligence-raises-500m-funding-round/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The announcement coincides with the U.S. debut of Ideally Canvas, a new product designed to replace static research snapshots with a &#8220;living dataset&#8221; of consumer insights.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was led by Shearwater Capital, with significant participation from Altered Capital, Icehouse Ventures, and Ecliptic VC. The investment values the company, which was founded just over two years ago in New Zealand, at more than $59 million (US).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Snapshot&#8221; Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Traditionally, market research has been a &#8220;waterfall&#8221; process: slow, expensive, and siloed. Brands often wait weeks or months for consumer feedback, by which time the creative direction is already locked in, or consumer sentiment has shifted.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ideally’s platform disrupts this by delivering real-world consumer feedback overnight. By utilizing AI to analyze responses from real humans across 30+ countries, Ideally provides actionable data in under 24 hours. The newly launched Ideally Canvas takes this a step further. Instead of treating every survey as a one-off project, Canvas treats research as a compounding asset. Every study conducted feeds into a continuous, living dataset that helps brands understand category dynamics and competitor shifts in real-time.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200176" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200176" class="wp-image-200176" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Ideally.jpeg" alt="Ideally" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-200176" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Ideally</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“The best creative work has always come from genuinely understanding real people, but that understanding has been locked behind months of waiting and six-figure budgets,” said James Donald, CEO of Ideally. “That world is over. We built Ideally to give every team that closeness at the speed and scale that modern markets actually demand.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/recursive-superintelligence-raises-500m-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Recursive Superintelligence Raises $500M Funding Round</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rapid U.S. Expansion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While Ideally established its dominance in the APAC region by partnering with heavyweights like DoorDash, Asahi, and Afterpay, the Series A capital is earmarked for an aggressive push into the North American market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Following the opening of its New York office earlier in 2026, Ideally has already reported a staggering 350% growth in US revenue. The platform is currently being used by a roster of prestigious global clients, including Google, Revlon, KFC, and Rémy Cointreau.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Joshua Nu’u-Steele, Co-Founder and Chief Revenue Officer, highlighted the urgency of the U.S. launch: “Every marketing leader I talk to in the U.S. has the same problem: their timelines are impossible, and they’re making million-dollar decisions on data that’s already six months old. That’s not a research problem; it’s a business problem.”</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Workflow for Creatives</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The &#8220;Canvas&#8221; product is specifically designed to sit at the earliest stages of the creative process. Rather than using research simply to validate a finished campaign, Ideally encourages &#8220;braver&#8221; decision-making by allowing strategists and creatives to test &#8220;half-baked&#8221; ideas early and often.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform’s AI doesn’t just summarize data; it identifies patterns, segments audiences, and even generates smarter follow-up questions based on actual respondent sentiment rather than &#8220;synthetic&#8221; or bot-generated personas. This ensures that while the speed is driven by AI, the insights remain anchored in authentic human behaviour.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As brands face a more fragmented media landscape and rapidly changing consumer tastes, Ideally’s move toward &#8220;always-on&#8221; insights marks a significant shift in the $90 billion global market research industry.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ideally-launches-ideally-canvas-after-10m-series-a/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ideally Launches Ideally Canvas After $10M Series A</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
