		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200167</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Coral Raises Funding To Fix Healthcare Administrative Delays Coral has raised $12.5 million in seed funding led by Lightspeed and Z47. The round includes several additional investors supporting early growth.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/coral-raises-12-5-million-to-automate-healthcare-administration/" data-wpel-link="internal">Coral Raises $12.5 Million To Automate Healthcare Administration</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Coral Raises Funding To Fix Healthcare Administrative Delays</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral has raised $12.5 million in seed funding led by Lightspeed and Z47. The round includes several additional investors supporting early growth. The funding positions the company to address one of healthcare’s largest inefficiencies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Administrative work remains a major burden across the healthcare system. These processes cost an estimated $450 billion each year. Delays often occur in referrals, prior authorisations, and patient intake workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many of these delays come from outdated systems still in use today. Fax machines remain central to many healthcare operations. This creates bottlenecks that slow patient care and increase operational pressure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral was founded in 2024 to address this challenge directly. The company focuses on automating workflows without replacing existing infrastructure. This approach allows providers to improve efficiency without disruption.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Platform Automates Fax-Based Healthcare Workflows</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral’s platform is built to work with existing healthcare systems. It connects with EHR systems, fax lines, and payer portals. This allows automation without requiring providers to change their workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system focuses on intake, prior authorisation, and patient communication. These processes often rely on manual input and fragmented data. Coral replaces these manual steps with automated actions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its AI models can process handwritten fax forms and scanned documents. It also reads insurance cards and payer portal data with high accuracy. The platform achieves accuracy levels of 99.7 percent across these document types.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This level of accuracy is critical in healthcare environments. Errors can lead to compliance issues or delays in treatment. Coral’s system ensures reliable processing across complex cases.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Patient intake times have improved significantly with the platform. Tasks that once took up to 30 minutes now take under five minutes. This reduces delays and allows staff to focus on patient care.</span></p>
<h2><b>High Accuracy Drives Adoption Across Healthcare Providers</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200169" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200169" class="size-full wp-image-200169" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Coral-2.png" alt="Healthcare AI system converting handwritten medical documents into structured digital data across hospitals, pharmacies, and care providers." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200169" class="wp-caption-text">Coral’s high-accuracy healthcare automation platform improving documentation speed and efficiency across medical providers. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral’s technology addresses the complexity of healthcare documentation. Many documents are unstructured and difficult to process. General automation tools often struggle in these environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform uses specialised models trained for healthcare workflows. These models handle handwritten forms and inconsistent data formats. This creates a reliable system for document processing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Early adoption has shown strong results across multiple use cases. Providers report faster turnaround times and improved operational efficiency. Some workflows that took hours now complete within minutes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customers have also shown strong confidence in the platform. Some are paying full contract value upfront. This is unusual in enterprise software and reflects immediate value delivery.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral’s early focus was on durable medical equipment providers. This sector relies heavily on fax-based workflows. The company has since expanded into infusion centres and specialty pharmacy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Each new sector presents similar administrative challenges. Coral applies the same automation model across these areas. This allows consistent performance across different healthcare workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/zenskar-raises-15m-ai-billing-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar Raises $15 Million To Expand AI Billing Automation Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>New Funding Supports Expansion And Product Development</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will support hiring across engineering and healthcare operations. Coral aims to build a team that understands both technology and industry needs. This combination is essential for scaling the platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is also expanding its product capabilities. It has introduced AI voice and text tools for follow-ups. These tools automate communication with patients and payers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Future updates include a workflow builder for healthcare providers. This feature will allow teams to create custom workflows without IT support. It will give providers greater control over their operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral is also developing analytics tools for operational insights. These tools will identify delays in authorisation processes. They will also highlight payers with high denial rates.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company aims to provide actionable intelligence for healthcare teams. Instead of static reports, users will receive clear next steps. This approach supports faster decision-making across operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coral believes administrative work is a </span><a href="https://www.simpplr.com/glossary/workflow/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">workflow</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> problem. Its platform focuses on improving processes rather than increasing staff. This approach helps reduce pressure across the healthcare system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company continues to expand across new healthcare sectors. It is targeting strong growth over the coming years. The funding provides the resources needed to scale its platform effectively.</span></p>
